â”‚     173â†’
â”‚     174â†’
â”‚     175â†’@chex.dataclass(frozen=True)
â”‚     176â†’class Stacking(je_base.BaseEnergyFunction):
â”‚     177â†’    """Stacking energy function for DNA1 model."""
â”‚     178â†’
â”‚     179â†’    params: StackingConfiguration
â”‚     180â†’
â”‚     181â†’    def compute_v_stack(
â”‚     182â†’        self,
â”‚     183â†’        stack_sites: typ.Arr_Nucleotide_3,
â”‚     184â†’        back_sites: typ.Arr_Nucleotide_3,
â”‚     185â†’        base_normals: typ.Arr_Nucleotide_3,
â”‚     186â†’        cross_prods: typ.Arr_Nucleotide_3,
â”‚     187â†’        bonded_neighbors: typ.Arr_Bonded_Neighbors_2,
â”‚     188â†’    ) -> typ.Arr_Bonded_Neighbors:
â”‚     189â†’        """Computes the sequence-independent energy for each bonded pair."""
â”‚     190â†’        nn_i = bonded_neighbors[:, 0]
â”‚     191â†’        nn_j = bonded_neighbors[:, 1]
â”‚     192â†’
â”‚     193â†’        dr_back_nn = self.displacement_mapped(back_sites[nn_i], back_sites[nn_j])  # N x N x 3
â”‚     194â†’        r_back_nn = jnp.linalg.norm(dr_back_nn, axis=1)
â”‚     195â†’
â”‚     196â†’        dr_stack_nn = self.displacement_mapped(stack_sites[nn_i], stack_sites[nn_j])
â”‚     197â†’        r_stack_nn = jnp.linalg.norm(dr_stack_nn, axis=1)
â”‚     198â†’        theta4 = jnp.arccos(jd_math.clamp(jnp.einsum("ij, ij->i", base_normals[nn_i], base_normals[nn_j])))
â”‚     199â†’        theta5 = jnp.pi - jnp.arccos(
â”‚     200â†’            jd_math.clamp(jnp.einsum("ij, ij->i", dr_stack_nn, base_normals[nn_j]) / r_stack_nn)
â”‚     201â†’        )
â”‚     202â†’        theta6 = jnp.pi - jnp.arccos(
â”‚     203â†’            jd_math.clamp(jnp.einsum("ij, ij->i", base_normals[nn_i], dr_stack_nn) / r_stack_nn)
â”‚     204â†’        )
â”‚     205â†’        cosphi1 = -jnp.einsum("ij, ij->i", cross_prods[nn_i], dr_back_nn) / r_back_nn
â”‚     206â†’        cosphi2 = -jnp.einsum("ij, ij->i", cross_prods[nn_j], dr_back_nn) / r_back_nn
â”‚     207â†’
â”‚     208â†’        return dna1_interactions.stacking(
â”‚     209â†’            r_stack_nn,
â”‚     210â†’            theta4,
â”‚     211â†’            theta5,
â”‚     212â†’            theta6,
â”‚     213â†’            cosphi1,
â”‚     214â†’            cosphi2,
â”‚     215â†’            self.params.dr_low_stack,
â”‚     216â†’            self.params.dr_high_stack,
â”‚     217â†’            self.params.eps_stack,
â”‚     218â†’            self.params.a_stack,
â”‚     219â†’            self.params.dr0_stack,
â”‚     220â†’            self.params.dr_c_stack,
â”‚     221â†’            self.params.dr_c_low_stack,
â”‚     222â†’            self.params.dr_c_high_stack,
â”‚     223â†’            self.params.b_low_stack,
â”‚     224â†’            self.params.b_high_stack,
â”‚     225â†’            self.params.theta0_stack_4,
â”‚     226â†’            self.params.delta_theta_star_stack_4,
â”‚     227â†’            self.params.a_stack_4,
â”‚     228â†’            self.params.delta_theta_stack_4_c,
â”‚     229â†’            self.params.b_stack_4,
â”‚     230â†’            self.params.theta0_stack_5,
â”‚     231â†’            self.params.delta_theta_star_stack_5,
â”‚     232â†’            self.params.a_stack_5,
â”‚     233â†’            self.params.delta_theta_stack_5_c,
â”‚     234â†’            self.params.b_stack_5,
â”‚     235â†’            self.params.theta0_stack_6,
â”‚     236â†’            self.params.delta_theta_star_stack_6,
â”‚     237â†’            self.params.a_stack_6,
â”‚     238â†’            self.params.delta_theta_stack_6_c,
â”‚     239â†’            self.params.b_stack_6,
â”‚     240â†’            self.params.neg_cos_phi1_star_stack,
â”‚     241â†’            self.params.a_stack_1,
â”‚     242â†’            self.params.neg_cos_phi1_c_stack,
â”‚     243â†’            self.params.b_neg_cos_phi1_stack,
â”‚     244â†’            self.params.neg_cos_phi2_star_stack,
â”‚     245â†’            self.params.a_stack_2,
â”‚     246â†’            self.params.neg_cos_phi2_c_stack,
â”‚     247â†’            self.params.b_neg_cos_phi2_stack,
â”‚     248â†’        )
â”‚     249â†’
â”‚     250â†’    def pairwise_energies(
â”‚     251â†’        self,
â”‚     252â†’        body: je_base.BaseNucleotide,
â”‚     253â†’        seq: typ.Discrete_Sequence,
â”‚     254â†’        bonded_neighbors: typ.Arr_Bonded_Neighbors_2,
â”‚     255â†’    ) -> typ.Arr_Bonded_Neighbors:
â”‚     256â†’        """Computes the stacking energy for each bonded pair."""
â”‚     257â†’        # Compute sequence-independent energy for each bonded pair
â”‚     258â†’        v_stack = self.compute_v_stack(
â”‚     259â†’            body.stack_sites, body.back_sites, body.base_normals, body.cross_prods, bonded_neighbors
â”‚     260â†’        )
â”‚     261â†’
â”‚     262â†’        # Compute sequence-dependent weight for each bonded pair
â”‚     263â†’        nn_i = bonded_neighbors[:, 0]
â”‚     264â†’        nn_j = bonded_neighbors[:, 1]
â”‚     265â†’        stack_weights = self.params.ss_stack_weights[seq[nn_i], seq[nn_j]]
â”‚     266â†’
â”‚     267â†’        return jnp.multiply(stack_weights, v_stack)
â”‚     268â†’
â”‚     269â†’    @override
â”‚     270â†’    def __call__(
â”‚     271â†’        self,
â”‚     272â†’        body: je_base.BaseNucleotide,
â”‚     273â†’        seq: typ.Discrete_Sequence,
â”‚     274â†’        bonded_neighbors: typ.Arr_Bonded_Neighbors_2,
â”‚     275â†’        unbonded_neighbors: typ.Arr_Unbonded_Neighbors_2,
â”‚     276â†’    ) -> typ.Scalar:
â”‚     277â†’        dgs = self.pairwise_energies(body, seq, bonded_neighbors)
â”‚     278â†’        return dgs.sum()
â”‚     279â†’
â”‚  
â”‚  <system-reminder>

â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€

â”Œâ”€ âœ… å·¥å…·è¾“å‡º [toolu_01W7U1]
â”‚       1â†’"""Nucleotide structure for DNA1 model - PyTorch/NPU version."""
â”‚       2â†’
â”‚       3â†’from dataclasses import dataclass
â”‚       4â†’from typing import Optional
â”‚       5â†’
â”‚       6â†’import torch
â”‚       7â†’
â”‚       8â†’from jax_dna_npu.energy.base import BaseNucleotide
â”‚       9â†’
â”‚      10â†’
â”‚      11â†’@dataclass
â”‚      12â†’class Nucleotide(BaseNucleotide):
â”‚      13â†’    """DNA1 nucleotide structure with center, backbone, and base sites.
â”‚      14â†’
â”‚      15â†’    This extends BaseNucleotide with DNA1-specific methods and properties.
â”‚      16â†’
â”‚      17â†’    Attributes:
â”‚      18â†’        centers: Center of mass positions (N, 3)
â”‚      19â†’        back_sites: Backbone site positions (N, 3)
â”‚      20â†’        base_sites: Base site positions (N, 3)
â”‚      21â†’        orientations: Optional orientation quaternions (N, 4)
â”‚      22â†’    """
â”‚      23â†’
â”‚      24â†’    @classmethod
â”‚      25â†’    def from_rigid_body(
â”‚      26â†’        cls,
â”‚      27â†’        centers: torch.Tensor,
â”‚      28â†’        quaternions: torch.Tensor,
â”‚      29â†’        offset_back: torch.Tensor = torch.tensor([0.0, 0.0, -0.4]),
â”‚      30â†’        offset_base: torch.Tensor = torch.tensor([0.0, 0.0, 0.4]),
â”‚      31â†’    ) -> "Nucleotide":
â”‚      32â†’        """Create nucleotide from rigid body representation.
â”‚      33â†’
â”‚      34â†’        Args:
â”‚      35â†’            centers: Center positions (N, 3)
â”‚      36â†’            quaternions: Orientation quaternions (N, 4)
â”‚      37â†’            offset_back: Backbone site offset in local frame
â”‚      38â†’            offset_base: Base site offset in local frame
â”‚      39â†’
â”‚      40â†’        Returns:
â”‚      41â†’            Nucleotide instance
â”‚      42â†’        """
â”‚      43â†’        # Rotate offsets by quaternions and add to centers
â”‚      44â†’        back_sites = centers + cls._rotate_by_quaternion(offset_back, quaternions)
â”‚      45â†’        base_sites = centers + cls._rotate_by_quaternion(offset_base, quaternions)
â”‚      46â†’
â”‚      47â†’        return cls(
â”‚      48â†’            centers=centers,
â”‚      49â†’            back_sites=back_sites,
â”‚      50â†’            base_sites=base_sites,
â”‚      51â†’            orientations=quaternions,
â”‚      52â†’        )
â”‚      53â†’
â”‚      54â†’    @staticmethod
â”‚      55â†’    def _rotate_by_quaternion(v: torch.Tensor, q: torch.Tensor) -> torch.Tensor:
â”‚      56â†’        """Rotate vector by quaternion.
â”‚      57â†’
â”‚      58â†’        Args:
â”‚      59â†’            v: Vector to rotate (3,) or (N, 3)
â”‚      60â†’            q: Quaternion (4,) or (N, 4) in [w, x, y, z] format
â”‚      61â†’
â”‚      62â†’        Returns:
â”‚      63â†’            Rotated vector
â”‚      64â†’        """
â”‚      65â†’        # Ensure inputs are the right shape
â”‚      66â†’        if v.dim() == 1:
â”‚      67â†’            v = v.unsqueeze(0)
â”‚      68â†’        if q.dim() == 1:
â”‚      69â†’            q = q.unsqueeze(0)
â”‚      70â†’
â”‚      71â†’        # Extract quaternion components (w, x, y, z)
â”‚      72â†’        w, x, y, z = q[:, 0], q[:, 1], q[:, 2], q[:, 3]
â”‚      73â†’
â”‚      74â†’        # Compute rotation matrix elements
â”‚      75â†’        r00 = 1 - 2*(y**2 + z**2)
â”‚      76â†’        r01 = 2*(x*y - w*z)
â”‚      77â†’        r02 = 2*(x*z + w*y)
â”‚      78â†’
â”‚      79â†’        r10 = 2*(x*y + w*z)
â”‚      80â†’        r11 = 1 - 2*(x**2 + z**2)
â”‚      81â†’        r12 = 2*(y*z - w*x)
â”‚      82â†’
â”‚      83â†’        r20 = 2*(x*z - w*y)
â”‚      84â†’        r21 = 2*(y*z + w*x)
â”‚      85â†’        r22 = 1 - 2*(x**2 + y**2)
â”‚      86â†’
â”‚      87â†’        # Apply rotation
â”‚      88â†’        vx, vy, vz = v[:, 0], v[:, 1], v[:, 2]
â”‚      89â†’        rx = r00*vx + r01*vy + r02*vz
â”‚      90â†’        ry = r10*vx + r11*vy + r12*vz
â”‚      91â†’        rz = r20*vx + r21*vy + r22*vz
â”‚      92â†’
â”‚      93â†’        return torch.stack([rx, ry, rz], dim=1)
â”‚      94â†’
â”‚      95â†’    @classmethod
â”‚      96â†’    def from_positions(
â”‚      97â†’        cls,
â”‚      98â†’        centers: torch.Tensor,
â”‚      99â†’        back_sites: torch.Tensor,
â”‚     100â†’        base_sites: torch.Tensor,
â”‚     101â†’    ) -> "Nucleotide":
â”‚     102â†’        """Create nucleotide from explicit site positions.
â”‚     103â†’
â”‚     104â†’        Args:
â”‚     105â†’            centers: Center positions (N, 3)
â”‚     106â†’            back_sites: Backbone site positions (N, 3)
â”‚     107â†’            base_sites: Base site positions (N, 3)
â”‚     108â†’
â”‚     109â†’        Returns:
â”‚     110â†’            Nucleotide instance
â”‚     111â†’        """
â”‚     112â†’        return cls(
â”‚     113â†’            centers=centers,
â”‚     114â†’            back_sites=back_sites,
â”‚     115â†’            base_sites=base_sites,
â”‚     116â†’            orientations=None,
â”‚     117â†’        )
â”‚     118â†’
â”‚     119â†’    def compute_vectors(self) -> dict[str, torch.Tensor]:
â”‚     120â†’        """Compute useful vectors between nucleotide sites.
â”‚     121â†’
â”‚     122â†’        Returns:
â”‚     123â†’            Dictionary with:
â”‚     124â†’            - dr_back: centers -> back_sites (N, 3)
â”‚     125â†’            - dr_base: centers -> base_sites (N, 3)
â”‚     126â†’            - dr_back_to_base: back_sites -> base_sites (N, 3)
â”‚     127â†’        """
â”‚     128â†’        return {
â”‚     129â†’            'dr_back': self.back_sites - self.centers,
â”‚     130â†’            'dr_base': self.base_sites - self.centers,
â”‚     131â†’            'dr_back_to_base': self.base_sites - self.back_sites,
â”‚     132â†’        }
â”‚     133â†’
â”‚     134â†’    def get_neighbor_vectors(
â”‚     135â†’        self,
â”‚     136â†’        neighbor_indices: torch.Tensor,
â”‚     137â†’    ) -> dict[str, torch.Tensor]:
â”‚     138â†’        """Compute vectors between neighboring nucleotides.
â”‚     139â†’
â”‚     140â†’        Args:
â”‚     141â†’            neighbor_indices: Neighbor pairs (M, 2)
â”‚     142â†’
â”‚     143â†’        Returns:
â”‚     144â†’            Dictionary of displacement vectors for each site type
â”‚     145â†’        """
â”‚     146â†’        i_idx = neighbor_indices[:, 0]
â”‚     147â†’        j_idx = neighbor_indices[:, 1]
â”‚     148â†’
â”‚     149â†’        return {
â”‚     150â†’            'dr_center': self.centers[j_idx] - self.centers[i_idx],
â”‚     151â†’            'dr_back': self.back_sites[j_idx] - self.back_sites[i_idx],
â”‚     152â†’            'dr_base': self.base_sites[j_idx] - self.base_sites[i_idx],
â”‚     153â†’            # Cross-site vectors
â”‚     154â†’            'dr_back_i_base_j': self.base_sites[j_idx] - self.back_sites[i_idx],
â”‚     155â†’            'dr_base_i_back_j': self.back_sites[j_idx] - self.base_sites[i_idx],
â”‚     156â†’        }
â”‚     157â†’
â”‚

â”‚      32â†’    def displacement_mapped(self) -> Callable:
â”‚      33â†’        """Returns the displacement function mapped to the space."""
â”‚      34â†’        return jax_md.space.map_bond(self.displacement_fn)
â”‚      35â†’
â”‚      36â†’    def __add__(self, other: "BaseEnergyFunction") -> "ComposedEnergyFunction":
â”‚      37â†’        """Add two energy functions together to create a ComposedEnergyFunction."""
â”‚      38â†’        if not isinstance(other, BaseEnergyFunction):
â”‚      39â†’            return NotImplemented
â”‚      40â†’
â”‚      41â†’        return ComposedEnergyFunction(energy_fns=[self, other])
â”‚      42â†’
â”‚      43â†’    def __mul__(self, other: float) -> "ComposedEnergyFunction":
â”‚      44â†’        """Multiply an energy function by a scalar to create a ComposedEnergyFunction."""
â”‚      45â†’        if not isinstance(other, float | int):
â”‚      46â†’            return NotImplemented
â”‚      47â†’

â”‚      64â†’@chex.dataclass(frozen=True)
â”‚      65â†’class ComposedEnergyFunction:
â”‚      66â†’    """Represents a linear combination of energy functions.
â”‚      67â†’
â”‚      68â†’    Parameters:
â”‚      69â†’        energy_fns (list[BaseEnergyFunction]): a list of energy functions
â”‚      70â†’        weights (jnp.ndarray): optional, the weights of the energy functions
â”‚      71â†’        rigid_body_transform_fn (Callable): a function to transform the rigid body
â”‚      72â†’        to into something that can be used by the energy functions like a DNA1 nucleotide
â”‚      73â†’    """
â”‚      74â†’
â”‚      75â†’    energy_fns: tuple[BaseEnergyFunction]
â”‚      76â†’    weights: jnp.ndarray | None = None

â”‚      78â†’
â”‚      79â†’    def __post_init__(self) -> None:
â”‚      80â†’        """Check that the input is valid."""
â”‚      81â†’        if not isinstance(self.energy_fns, list) or not all(
â”‚      82â†’            isinstance(fn, BaseEnergyFunction) for fn in self.energy_fns
â”‚      83â†’        ):
â”‚      84â†’            raise TypeError(ERR_COMPOSED_ENERGY_FN_TYPE_ENERGY_FNS)
â”‚      85â†’
â”‚      86â†’        if self.weights is not None and len(self.weights) != len(self.energy_fns):
â”‚      87â†’            raise ValueError(ERR_COMPOSED_ENERGY_FN_LEN_MISMATCH)
â”‚      88â†’
â”‚      89â†’    def compute_terms(
â”‚      90â†’        self,
â”‚      91â†’        body: jax_md.rigid_body.RigidBody,
â”‚      92â†’        seq: typ.Sequence,
â”‚      93â†’        bonded_neighbors: typ.Arr_Bonded_Neighbors_2,
â”‚      94â†’        unbonded_neighbors: typ.Arr_Unbonded_Neighbors_2,
â”‚      95â†’    ) -> jnp.ndarray:
â”‚      96â†’        """Compute each of the energy terms in the energy function."""
â”‚      97â†’        if self.rigid_body_transform_fn:
â”‚      98â†’            body = self.rigid_body_transform_fn(body)
â”‚      99â†’
â”‚     100â†’        return jnp.array([fn(body, seq, bonded_neighbors, unbonded_neighbors) for fn in self.energy_fns])
â”‚     101â†’
â”‚     102â†’    def __call__(
â”‚     103â†’        self,
â”‚     104â†’        body: jax_md.rigid_body.RigidBody,
â”‚     105â†’        seq: typ.Sequence,
â”‚     106â†’        bonded_neighbors: typ.Arr_Bonded_Neighbors_2,
â”‚     107â†’        unbonded_neighbors: typ.Arr_Unbonded_Neighbors_2,
â”‚     108â†’    ) -> float:
â”‚     109â†’        """Calculates the energy of the system using the all of the function in `energy_fns`.
â”‚     110â†’
â”‚     111â†’        Args:
â”‚     112â†’            body (jax_md.rigid_body.RigidBody): The rigid body(ies) of the system
â”‚     113â†’            seq (typ.Sequence): the sequence of the system
â”‚     114â†’            bonded_neighbors (typ.Arr_Bonded_Neighbors_2): the bonded neighbors
â”‚     115â†’            unbonded_neighbors (typ.Arr_Unbonded_Neighbors_2): the unbonded neighbors
â”‚     116â†’
â”‚     117â†’        Returns:
â”‚     118â†’            float: the energy of the system
â”‚     119â†’        """
â”‚     120â†’        energy_vals = self.compute_terms(body, seq, bonded_neighbors, unbonded_neighbors)
â”‚     121â†’        return jnp.sum(energy_vals) if self.weights is None else jnp.dot(self.weights, energy_vals)
â”‚     122â†’
â”‚     123â†’    def add_energy_fn(self, energy_fn: BaseEnergyFunction, weight: float = 1.0) -> "ComposedEnergyFunction":
â”‚     124â†’        """Add an energy function to the list of energy functions.
â”‚     125â†’
â”‚     126â†’        Args:
â”‚     127â†’            energy_fn (BaseEnergyFunction): the energy function to add
â”‚     128â†’            weight (float): the weight of the energy function
â”‚     129â†’
â”‚     130â†’        Returns:
â”‚     131â†’            ComposedEnergyFunction: a new ComposedEnergyFunction with the added energy function
â”‚     132â†’        """
â”‚     133â†’        if self.weights is None:
â”‚     134â†’            weights = None if weight == 1.0 else jnp.array([1.0] * len(self.energy_fns) + [weight])
â”‚     135â†’        else:
â”‚     136â†’            weights = jnp.concatenate([self.weights, jnp.array([weight])])
â”‚     137â†’
â”‚     138â†’        return ComposedEnergyFunction(
â”‚     139â†’            energy_fns=[*self.energy_fns, energy_fn],
â”‚     140â†’            weights=weights,
â”‚     141â†’        )

â”‚       8â†’from jax import vmap
â”‚       9â†’
â”‚      10â†’import jax_dna.utils.constants as jd_const
â”‚      11â†’import jax_dna.utils.types as typ
â”‚      12â†’
â”‚      13â†’
â”‚      14â†’@vmap
â”‚      15â†’def q_to_back_base(q: jax_md.rigid_body.Quaternion) -> jnp.ndarray:
â”‚      16â†’    """Get the vector from the center to the base of the nucleotide."""
â”‚      17â†’    q0, q1, q2, q3 = q.vec
â”‚      18â†’    return jnp.array([q0**2 + q1**2 - q2**2 - q3**2, 2 * (q1 * q2 + q0 * q3), 2 * (q1 * q3 - q0 * q2)])
â”‚      19â†’
â”‚      20â†’
â”‚      21â†’@vmap
â”‚      22â†’def q_to_base_normal(q: jax_md.rigid_body.Quaternion) -> jnp.ndarray:
â”‚      23â†’    """Get the normal vector to the base of the nucleotide."""
â”‚      24â†’    q0, q1, q2, q3 = q.vec
â”‚      25â†’    return jnp.array([2 * (q1 * q3 + q0 * q2), 2 * (q2 * q3 - q0 * q1), q0**2 - q1**2 - q2**2 + q3**2])
â”‚      26â†’
â”‚      27â†’
â”‚      28â†’@vmap
â”‚      29â†’def q_to_cross_prod(q: jax_md.rigid_body.Quaternion) -> jnp.ndarray:
â”‚      30â†’    """Get the cross product vector of the nucleotide."""
â”‚      31â†’    q0, q1, q2, q3 = q.vec
â”‚      32â†’    return jnp.array([2 * (q1 * q2 - q0 * q3), q0**2 - q1**2 + q2**2 - q3**2, 2 * (q2 * q3 + q0 * q1)])
â”‚      33â†’
â”‚      34â†’
â”‚      35â†’@functools.partial(vmap, in_axes=(None, 0, 0), out_axes=0)
â”‚      36â†’def get_pair_probs(seq: typ.Arr_Nucleotide_4, i: int, j: int) -> jnp.ndarray:
â”‚      37â†’    """Get the pair probabilities for a sequence."""
â”‚      38â†’    return jnp.kron(seq[i], seq[j])
â”‚      39â†’
â”‚      40â†’
â”‚      41â†’def compute_seq_dep_weight(
â”‚      42â†’    pseq: typ.Probabilistic_Sequence,
â”‚      43â†’    nt1: int,
â”‚      44â†’    nt2: int,
â”‚      45â†’    weights_table: np.ndarray,
â”‚      46â†’    is_unpaired: typ.Arr_Nucleotide_Int,
â”‚      47â†’    idx_to_unpaired_idx: typ.Arr_Nucleotide_Int,
â”‚      48â†’    idx_to_bp_idx: typ.Arr_Nucleotide_2_Int,
â”‚      49â†’) -> float:
â”‚      50â†’    """Computes the sequence-dependent weight for an interaction given a probabilistic sequence."""
â”‚      51â†’    unpaired_pseq, bp_pseq = pseq
â”‚      52â†’    flattened_weights_table = weights_table.flatten()
â”‚      53â†’
â”‚      54â†’    nt1_unpaired = is_unpaired[nt1]
â”‚      55â†’    nt2_unpaired = is_unpaired[nt2]
â”‚      56â†’
â”‚      57â†’    # Case 1: Both unpaired
â”‚      58â†’    pair_probs = jnp.kron(unpaired_pseq[idx_to_unpaired_idx[nt1]], unpaired_pseq[idx_to_unpaired_idx[nt2]])
â”‚      59â†’    pair_weight_unpaired = jnp.dot(pair_probs, flattened_weights_table)
â”‚      60â†’
â”‚      61â†’    # Case 2: nt1 unpaired, nt2 base paired
â”‚      62â†’    nt1_nt_probs = unpaired_pseq[idx_to_unpaired_idx[nt1]]
â”‚      63â†’    nt2_bp_idx, within_nt2_bp_idx = idx_to_bp_idx[nt2]
â”‚      64â†’    bp_probs = bp_pseq[nt2_bp_idx]
â”‚      65â†’
â”‚      66â†’    def nt1_up_fn(nt1_nt: int, nt2_bp_type_idx: int) -> float:
â”‚      67â†’        nt2_nt = jd_const.BP_IDXS[nt2_bp_type_idx][within_nt2_bp_idx]
â”‚      68â†’        return nt1_nt_probs[nt1_nt] * bp_probs[nt2_bp_type_idx] * weights_table[nt1_nt, nt2_nt]
â”‚      69â†’
â”‚      70â†’    pair_weight_nt1_up = vmap(vmap(nt1_up_fn, (None, 0)), (0, None))(
â”‚      71â†’        jnp.arange(jd_const.N_NT), jnp.arange(jd_const.N_BP_TYPES)
â”‚      72â†’    ).sum()
â”‚      73â†’
â”‚      74â†’    # Case 3: nt2 unpaired, nt1 base paired
â”‚      75â†’
â”‚      76â†’    nt2_nt_probs = unpaired_pseq[idx_to_unpaired_idx[nt2]]
â”‚      77â†’    nt1_bp_idx, within_nt1_bp_idx = idx_to_bp_idx[nt1]
â”‚      78â†’    bp_probs = bp_pseq[nt1_bp_idx]
â”‚      79â†’
â”‚      80â†’    def nt2_up_fn(nt2_nt: int, nt1_bp_type_idx: int) -> float:
â”‚      81â†’        nt1_nt = jd_const.BP_IDXS[nt1_bp_type_idx][within_nt1_bp_idx]
â”‚      82â†’        return nt2_nt_probs[nt2_nt] * bp_probs[nt1_bp_type_idx] * weights_table[nt1_nt, nt2_nt]
â”‚      83â†’
â”‚      84â†’    pair_weight_nt2_up = vmap(vmap(nt2_up_fn, (None, 0)), (0, None))(
â”‚      85â†’        jnp.arange(jd_const.N_NT), jnp.arange(jd_const.N_BP_TYPES)
â”‚      86â†’    ).sum()
â”‚      87â†’
â”‚      88â†’    # Case 4: both nt1 and nt2 are base paired
â”‚      89â†’
â”‚      90â†’    nt1_bp_idx, within_nt1_bp_idx = idx_to_bp_idx[nt1]
â”‚      91â†’    nt2_bp_idx, within_nt2_bp_idx = idx_to_bp_idx[nt2]
â”‚      92â†’
â”‚      93â†’    ## Case 4.I: nt1 and nt2 are in the same base pair
â”‚      94â†’    bp_probs = bp_pseq[nt1_bp_idx]
â”‚      95â†’
â”‚      96â†’    def same_bp_fn(bp_idx: int) -> float:
â”‚      97â†’        bp_prob = bp_probs[bp_idx]
â”‚      98â†’        bp_nt1, bp_nt2 = jd_const.BP_IDXS[bp_idx][jnp.array([within_nt1_bp_idx, within_nt2_bp_idx])]
â”‚      99â†’        return bp_prob * weights_table[bp_nt1, bp_nt2]
â”‚     100â†’
â”‚     101â†’    pair_weight_same_bp = vmap(same_bp_fn)(jnp.arange(jd_const.N_BP_TYPES)).sum()
â”‚     102â†’
â”‚     103â†’    ## Case 4.II: nt1 and nt2 are in different base pairs
â”‚     104â†’    bp1_probs = bp_pseq[nt1_bp_idx]
â”‚     105â†’    bp2_probs = bp_pseq[nt2_bp_idx]
â”‚     106â†’
â”‚     107â†’    def diff_bps_fn(bp1_idx: int, bp2_idx: int) -> float:
â”‚     108â†’        bp1_prob = bp1_probs[bp1_idx]
â”‚     109â†’        nt1_nt = jd_const.BP_IDXS[bp1_idx][within_nt1_bp_idx]
â”‚     110â†’
â”‚     111â†’        bp2_prob = bp2_probs[bp2_idx]
â”‚     112â†’        nt2_nt = jd_const.BP_IDXS[bp2_idx][within_nt2_bp_idx]
â”‚     113â†’
â”‚     114â†’        return bp1_prob * bp2_prob * weights_table[nt1_nt, nt2_nt]
â”‚     115â†’
â”‚     116â†’    pair_weight_diff_bps = vmap(vmap(diff_bps_fn, (None, 0)), (0, None))(
â”‚     117â†’        jnp.arange(jd_const.N_BP_TYPES), jnp.arange(jd_const.N_BP_TYPES)
â”‚     118â†’    ).sum()
â”‚     119â†’
â”‚     120â†’    pair_weight_both_paired = jnp.where(nt1_bp_idx == nt2_bp_idx, pair_weight_same_bp, pair_weight_diff_bps)
â”‚     121â†’
â”‚     122â†’    return jnp.where(
â”‚     123â†’        jnp.logical_and(nt1_unpaired, nt2_unpaired),
â”‚     124â†’        pair_weight_unpaired,
â”‚     125â†’        jnp.where(
â”‚     126â†’            nt1_unpaired, pair_weight_nt1_up, jnp.where(nt2_unpaired, pair_weight_nt2_up, pair_weight_both_paired)
â”‚     127â†’        ),
â”‚     128â†’    )
â”‚     129â†’
â”‚

"""Utility functions for DNA1 energy calculations - PyTorch/NPU version."""

import torch


def q_to_back_base(q: torch.Tensor) -> torch.Tensor:
    """Get the vector from the center to the base of the nucleotide.
    
    Args:
        q: Quaternion(s) in [w, x, y, z] format (N, 4) or (4,)
        
    Returns:
        Back-base vector(s) (N, 3) or (3,)
    """
    if q.dim() == 1:
        q = q.unsqueeze(0)
        squeeze = True
    else:
        squeeze = False
    
    q0, q1, q2, q3 = q[:, 0], q[:, 1], q[:, 2], q[:, 3]
    
    result = torch.stack([
        q0**2 + q1**2 - q2**2 - q3**2,
        2 * (q1 * q2 + q0 * q3),
        2 * (q1 * q3 - q0 * q2)
    ], dim=1)
    
    return result.squeeze(0) if squeeze else result


def q_to_base_normal(q: torch.Tensor) -> torch.Tensor:
    """Get the normal vector to the base of the nucleotide.
    
    Args:
        q: Quaternion(s) in [w, x, y, z] format (N, 4) or (4,)
        
    Returns:
        Base normal vector(s) (N, 3) or (3,)
    """
    if q.dim() == 1:
        q = q.unsqueeze(0)
        squeeze = True
    else:
        squeeze = False
    
    q0, q1, q2, q3 = q[:, 0], q[:, 1], q[:, 2], q[:, 3]
    
    result = torch.stack([
        2 * (q1 * q3 + q0 * q2),
        2 * (q2 * q3 - q0 * q1),
        q0**2 - q1**2 - q2**2 + q3**2
    ], dim=1)
    
    return result.squeeze(0) if squeeze else result


def q_to_cross_prod(q: torch.Tensor) -> torch.Tensor:
    """Get the cross product vector of the nucleotide.
    
    Args:
        q: Quaternion(s) in [w, x, y, z] format (N, 4) or (4,)
        
    Returns:
        Cross product vector(s) (N, 3) or (3,)
    """
    if q.dim() == 1:
        q = q.unsqueeze(0)
        squeeze = True
    else:
        squeeze = False
    
    q0, q1, q2, q3 = q[:, 0], q[:, 1], q[:, 2], q[:, 3]
    
    result = torch.stack([
        2 * (q1 * q2 - q0 * q3),
        q0**2 - q1**2 + q2**2 - q3**2,
        2 * (q2 * q3 + q0 * q1)
    ], dim=1)
    
    return result.squeeze(0) if squeeze else result

â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€

"""Stacking energy function for DNA1 model - PyTorch NPU version."""

from dataclasses import dataclass, field
from typing import Optional
import torch
import numpy as np

from jax_dna_npu.energy.base import BaseEnergyFunction
from jax_dna_npu.energy.configuration import BaseConfiguration
from jax_dna_npu.energy.dna1.nucleotide import Nucleotide
import jax_dna_npu.energy.dna1.base_smoothing_functions as bsf
import jax_dna_npu.energy.dna1.interactions as dna1_interactions
import jax_dna_npu.utils.math as jd_math
import jax_dna_npu.utils.types as typ


# Default stack weights (sequence-averaged)
STACK_WEIGHTS_SA = torch.tensor([
    [1.0, 1.0, 1.0, 1.0],  # AX
    [1.0, 1.0, 1.0, 1.0],  # CX
    [1.0, 1.0, 1.0, 1.0],  # GX
    [1.0, 1.0, 1.0, 1.0],  # TX
])


@dataclass
class StackingConfiguration(BaseConfiguration):
    """Configuration for the stacking energy function."""

    # Independent parameters
    eps_stack_base: Optional[float] = None
    eps_stack_kt_coeff: Optional[float] = None
    dr_low_stack: Optional[float] = None
    dr_high_stack: Optional[float] = None
    a_stack: Optional[float] = None
    dr0_stack: Optional[float] = None
    dr_c_stack: Optional[float] = None
    theta0_stack_4: Optional[float] = None
    delta_theta_star_stack_4: Optional[float] = None
    a_stack_4: Optional[float] = None
    theta0_stack_5: Optional[float] = None
    delta_theta_star_stack_5: Optional[float] = None
    a_stack_5: Optional[float] = None
    theta0_stack_6: Optional[float] = None
    delta_theta_star_stack_6: Optional[float] = None
    a_stack_6: Optional[float] = None
    neg_cos_phi1_star_stack: Optional[float] = None
    a_stack_1: Optional[float] = None
    neg_cos_phi2_star_stack: Optional[float] = None
    a_stack_2: Optional[float] = None
    kt: Optional[float] = None
    ss_stack_weights: Optional[np.ndarray] = None

    # Dependent parameters
    b_low_stack: Optional[float] = None
    dr_c_low_stack: Optional[float] = None
    b_high_stack: Optional[float] = None
    dr_c_high_stack: Optional[float] = None
    b_stack_4: Optional[float] = None
    delta_theta_stack_4_c: Optional[float] = None
    b_stack_5: Optional[float] = None
    delta_theta_stack_5_c: Optional[float] = None
    b_stack_6: Optional[float] = None
    delta_theta_stack_6_c: Optional[float] = None
    b_neg_cos_phi1_stack: Optional[float] = None
    neg_cos_phi1_c_stack: Optional[float] = None
    b_neg_cos_phi2_stack: Optional[float] = None
    neg_cos_phi2_c_stack: Optional[float] = None
    eps_stack: Optional[float] = None

    required_params: tuple[str, ...] = (
        "eps_stack_base",
        "eps_stack_kt_coeff",
        "dr_low_stack",
        "dr_high_stack",
        "a_stack",
        "dr0_stack",
        "dr_c_stack",
        "theta0_stack_4",
        "delta_theta_star_stack_4",
        "a_stack_4",
        "theta0_stack_5",
        "delta_theta_star_stack_5",
        "a_stack_5",
        "theta0_stack_6",
        "delta_theta_star_stack_6",
        "a_stack_6",
        "neg_cos_phi1_star_stack",
        "a_stack_1",
        "neg_cos_phi2_star_stack",
        "a_stack_2",
        "kt",
    )

    dependent_params: tuple[str, ...] = (
        "b_low_stack",
        "dr_c_low_stack",
        "b_high_stack",
        "dr_c_high_stack",
        "b_stack_4",
        "delta_theta_stack_4_c",
        "b_stack_5",
        "delta_theta_stack_5_c",
        "b_stack_6",
        "delta_theta_stack_6_c",
        "b_neg_cos_phi1_stack",
        "neg_cos_phi1_c_stack",
        "b_neg_cos_phi2_stack",
        "neg_cos_phi2_c_stack",
        "eps_stack",
    )

    def __post_init__(self):
        """Initialize default stack weights if not provided."""
        if self.ss_stack_weights is None:
            object.__setattr__(self, 'ss_stack_weights', STACK_WEIGHTS_SA.numpy())

    def init_params(self) -> "StackingConfiguration":
        """Initialize dependent parameters from independent parameters."""
        eps_stack = self.eps_stack_base + self.eps_stack_kt_coeff * self.kt

        b_low_stack, dr_c_low_stack, b_high_stack, dr_c_high_stack = bsf.get_f1_smoothing_params(
            self.dr0_stack,
            self.a_stack,
            self.dr_c_stack,
            self.dr_low_stack,
            self.dr_high_stack,
        )

        b_stack_4, delta_theta_stack_4_c = bsf.get_f4_smoothing_params(
            self.a_stack_4,
            self.theta0_stack_4,
            self.delta_theta_star_stack_4,
        )

        b_stack_5, delta_theta_stack_5_c = bsf.get_f4_smoothing_params(
            self.a_stack_5,
            self.theta0_stack_5,
            self.delta_theta_star_stack_5,
        )

        b_stack_6, delta_theta_stack_6_c = bsf.get_f4_smoothing_params(
            self.a_stack_6,
            self.theta0_stack_6,
            self.delta_theta_star_stack_6,
        )

        b_neg_cos_phi1_stack, neg_cos_phi1_c_stack = bsf.get_f5_smoothing_params(
            self.a_stack_1,
            self.neg_cos_phi1_star_stack,
        )

        b_neg_cos_phi2_stack, neg_cos_phi2_c_stack = bsf.get_f5_smoothing_params(
            self.a_stack_2,
            self.neg_cos_phi2_star_stack,
        )

        # Convert tensors to floats
        def to_float(x):
            return float(x.item()) if isinstance(x, torch.Tensor) else float(x)

        return StackingConfiguration(
            params_to_optimize=self.params_to_optimize,
            required_params=self.required_params,
            non_optimizable_required_params=self.non_optimizable_required_params,
            dependent_params=self.dependent_params,
            eps_stack_base=self.eps_stack_base,
            eps_stack_kt_coeff=self.eps_stack_kt_coeff,
            dr_low_stack=self.dr_low_stack,
            dr_high_stack=self.dr_high_stack,
            a_stack=self.a_stack,
            dr0_stack=self.dr0_stack,
            dr_c_stack=self.dr_c_stack,
            theta0_stack_4=self.theta0_stack_4,
            delta_theta_star_stack_4=self.delta_theta_star_stack_4,
            a_stack_4=self.a_stack_4,
            theta0_stack_5=self.theta0_stack_5,
            delta_theta_star_stack_5=self.delta_theta_star_stack_5,
            a_stack_5=self.a_stack_5,
            theta0_stack_6=self.theta0_stack_6,
            delta_theta_star_stack_6=self.delta_theta_star_stack_6,
            a_stack_6=self.a_stack_6,
            neg_cos_phi1_star_stack=self.neg_cos_phi1_star_stack,
            a_stack_1=self.a_stack_1,
            neg_cos_phi2_star_stack=self.neg_cos_phi2_star_stack,
            a_stack_2=self.a_stack_2,
            kt=self.kt,
            ss_stack_weights=self.ss_stack_weights,
            b_low_stack=to_float(b_low_stack),
            dr_c_low_stack=to_float(dr_c_low_stack),
            b_high_stack=to_float(b_high_stack),
            dr_c_high_stack=to_float(dr_c_high_stack),
            b_stack_4=to_float(b_stack_4),
            delta_theta_stack_4_c=to_float(delta_theta_stack_4_c),
            b_stack_5=to_float(b_stack_5),
            delta_theta_stack_5_c=to_float(delta_theta_stack_5_c),
            b_stack_6=to_float(b_stack_6),
            delta_theta_stack_6_c=to_float(delta_theta_stack_6_c),
            b_neg_cos_phi1_stack=to_float(b_neg_cos_phi1_stack),
            neg_cos_phi1_c_stack=to_float(neg_cos_phi1_c_stack),
            b_neg_cos_phi2_stack=to_float(b_neg_cos_phi2_stack),
            neg_cos_phi2_c_stack=to_float(neg_cos_phi2_c_stack),
            eps_stack=to_float(eps_stack),
        )


class Stacking(BaseEnergyFunction):
    """Stacking energy function for DNA1 model."""

    def __init__(self, params: StackingConfiguration, displacement_fn=None):
        """Initialize the stacking energy function.

        Args:
            params: Configuration parameters
            displacement_fn: Optional custom displacement function
        """
        super().__init__(displacement_fn)
        self.params = params

        # Initialize dependent parameters if needed
        if any(getattr(params, name) is None for name in params.dependent_params):
            self.params = params.init_params()

        # Register optimizable parameters
        if params.params_to_optimize:
            for name, value in params.opt_params_torch.items():
                self.register_parameter(f'param_{name}', value)

        # Register stack weights as buffer (not trainable by default)
        if params.ss_stack_weights is not None:
            self.register_buffer(
                'stack_weights',
                torch.as_tensor(params.ss_stack_weights, dtype=torch.float32)
            )
        else:
            self.register_buffer('stack_weights', STACK_WEIGHTS_SA)

    def compute_v_stack(
        self,
        stack_sites: torch.Tensor,
        back_sites: torch.Tensor,
        base_normals: torch.Tensor,
        cross_prods: torch.Tensor,
        bonded_neighbors: torch.Tensor,
    ) -> torch.Tensor:
        """Compute the sequence-independent energy for each bonded pair.

        Args:
            stack_sites: Stacking site positions (N, 3)
            back_sites: Backbone site positions (N, 3)
            base_normals: Base normal vectors (N, 3)
            cross_prods: Cross product vectors (N, 3)
            bonded_neighbors: Bonded neighbor pairs (M, 2)

        Returns:
            Energy for each bonded pair (M,)
        """
        nn_i = bonded_neighbors[:, 0].long()
        nn_j = bonded_neighbors[:, 1].long()

        # Displacement vectors
        dr_back_nn = self._displacement_fn(back_sites[nn_i], back_sites[nn_j])
        r_back_nn = torch.linalg.norm(dr_back_nn, dim=1)

        dr_stack_nn = self._displacement_fn(stack_sites[nn_i], stack_sites[nn_j])
        r_stack_nn = torch.linalg.norm(dr_stack_nn, dim=1)

        # Compute angles
        theta4 = torch.arccos(
            jd_math.clamp(torch.einsum("ij, ij->i", base_normals[nn_i], base_normals[nn_j]))
        )
        theta5 = torch.pi - torch.arccos(
            jd_math.clamp(torch.einsum("ij, ij->i", dr_stack_nn, base_normals[nn_j]) / r_stack_nn)
        )
        theta6 = torch.pi - torch.arccos(
            jd_math.clamp(torch.einsum("ij, ij->i", base_normals[nn_i], dr_stack_nn) / r_stack_nn)
        )
        cosphi1 = -torch.einsum("ij, ij->i", cross_prods[nn_i], dr_back_nn) / r_back_nn
        cosphi2 = -torch.einsum("ij, ij->i", cross_prods[nn_j], dr_back_nn) / r_back_nn

        return dna1_interactions.stacking(
            r_stack_nn,
            theta4,
            theta5,
            theta6,
            cosphi1,
            cosphi2,
            self.params.dr_low_stack,
            self.params.dr_high_stack,
            self.params.eps_stack,
            self.params.a_stack,
            self.params.dr0_stack,
            self.params.dr_c_stack,
            self.params.dr_c_low_stack,
            self.params.dr_c_high_stack,
            self.params.b_low_stack,
            self.params.b_high_stack,
            self.params.theta0_stack_4,
            self.params.delta_theta_star_stack_4,
            self.params.a_stack_4,
            self.params.delta_theta_stack_4_c,
            self.params.b_stack_4,
            self.params.theta0_stack_5,
            self.params.delta_theta_star_stack_5,
            self.params.a_stack_5,
            self.params.delta_theta_stack_5_c,
            self.params.b_stack_5,
            self.params.theta0_stack_6,
            self.params.delta_theta_star_stack_6,
            self.params.a_stack_6,
            self.params.delta_theta_stack_6_c,
            self.params.b_stack_6,
            self.params.neg_cos_phi1_star_stack,
            self.params.a_stack_1,
            self.params.neg_cos_phi1_c_stack,
            self.params.b_neg_cos_phi1_stack,
            self.params.neg_cos_phi2_star_stack,
            self.params.a_stack_2,
            self.params.neg_cos_phi2_c_stack,
            self.params.b_neg_cos_phi2_stack,
        )

    def pairwise_energies(
        self,
        nucleotides: Nucleotide,
        seq: typ.Sequence,
        bonded_neighbors: torch.Tensor,
    ) -> torch.Tensor:
        """Compute the stacking energy for each bonded pair.

        Args:
            nucleotides: Nucleotide structure
            seq: Nucleotide sequence
            bonded_neighbors: Bonded neighbor pairs (M, 2)

        Returns:
            Energy for each bonded pair (M,)
        """
        # Compute sequence-independent energy for each bonded pair
        v_stack = self.compute_v_stack(
            nucleotides.stack_sites,
            nucleotides.back_sites,
            nucleotides.base_normals,
            nucleotides.cross_prods,
            bonded_neighbors,
        )

        # Compute sequence-dependent weight for each bonded pair
        nn_i = bonded_neighbors[:, 0].long()
        nn_j = bonded_neighbors[:, 1].long()
        
        # Convert sequence to tensor if needed
        if isinstance(seq, (list, tuple)):
            seq = torch.tensor(seq, dtype=torch.long)
        
        stack_weights = self.stack_weights[seq[nn_i], seq[nn_j]]

        return stack_weights * v_stack

    def forward(
        self,
        positions: torch.Tensor,
        seq: typ.Sequence,
        bonded_neighbors: torch.Tensor,
        unbonded_neighbors: torch.Tensor,
        nucleotides: Optional[Nucleotide] = None,
        **kwargs
    ) -> torch.Tensor:
        """Calculate total stacking energy.

        Args:
            positions: Nucleotide positions (can be centers or full structure)
            seq: Nucleotide sequence
            bonded_neighbors: Bonded neighbor pairs (M, 2)
            unbonded_neighbors: Unbonded neighbor pairs (not used)
            nucleotides: Optional precomputed nucleotide structure
            **kwargs: Additional parameters

        Returns:
            Total stacking energy (scalar tensor)
        """
        # If nucleotides not provided, assume positions are Nucleotide object
        if nucleotides is None:
            # Use attribute checking instead of isinstance to handle device transfers
            if hasattr(positions, 'stack_sites') and hasattr(positions, 'base_normals'):
                nucleotides = positions
            else:
                raise ValueError("Stacking energy requires full Nucleotide structure with stack_sites and base_normals")

        # Verify required attributes exist
        if nucleotides.stack_sites is None or nucleotides.base_normals is None:
            raise ValueError("Stacking energy requires Nucleotide with stack_sites and base_normals computed")

        # Compute pairwise energies and sum
        dgs = self.pairwise_energies(nucleotides, seq, bonded_neighbors)
        return dgs.sum()
EOF

Add DNA1 excluded volume and stacking energy classes

- Implement BondedExcludedVolume with f3 smoothing
- Implement UnbondedExcludedVolume with masking support  
- Implement Stacking with sequence-dependent weights
- Create DNA1 utils with quaternion conversion functions (q_to_back_base, q_to_base_normal, q_to_cross_prod)
- Extend Nucleotide class with stacking-related attributes (stack_sites, base_normals, cross_prods)
- Update from_rigid_body to compute all directional vectors from quaternions

All classes follow PyTorch nn.Module architecture and support NPU devices.

ğŸ¤– Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)

Co-Authored-By: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
EOF

â”‚     216â†’class HydrogenBonding(je_base.BaseEnergyFunction):
â”‚     217â†’    """Hydrogen bonding energy function for DNA1 model."""
â”‚     218â†’
â”‚     219â†’    params: HydrogenBondingConfiguration
â”‚     220â†’
â”‚     221â†’    def compute_v_hb(
â”‚     222â†’        self,
â”‚     223â†’        body_i: je_base.BaseNucleotide,
â”‚     224â†’        body_j: je_base.BaseNucleotide,
â”‚     225â†’        unbonded_neighbors: typ.Arr_Unbonded_Neighbors,
â”‚     226â†’    ) -> typ.Arr_Unbonded_Neighbors:
â”‚     227â†’        """Computes the sequence-independent energy for each unbonded pair."""
â”‚     228â†’        op_i = unbonded_neighbors[0]
â”‚     229â†’        op_j = unbonded_neighbors[1]
â”‚     230â†’        mask = jnp.array(op_i < body_i.center.shape[0], dtype=jnp.float64)
â”‚     231â†’
â”‚     232â†’        dr_base_op = self.displacement_mapped(body_j.base_sites[op_j], body_i.base_sites[op_i])
â”‚     233â†’        r_base_op = jnp.linalg.norm(dr_base_op, axis=1)
â”‚     234â†’
â”‚     235â†’        theta1_op = jnp.arccos(
â”‚     236â†’            jd_math.clamp(jd_math.mult(-body_i.back_base_vectors[op_i], body_j.back_base_vectors[op_j]))
â”‚     237â†’        )
â”‚     238â†’        theta2_op = jnp.arccos(jd_math.clamp(jd_math.mult(-body_j.back_base_vectors[op_j], dr_base_op) / r_base_op))
â”‚     239â†’        theta3_op = jnp.arccos(jd_math.clamp(jd_math.mult(body_i.back_base_vectors[op_i], dr_base_op) / r_base_op))
â”‚     240â†’        theta4_op = jnp.arccos(jd_math.clamp(jd_math.mult(body_i.base_normals[op_i], body_j.base_normals[op_j])))
â”‚     241â†’        # note: are these swapped in Lorenzo's code?
â”‚     242â†’        theta7_op = jnp.arccos(jd_math.clamp(jd_math.mult(-body_j.base_normals[op_j], dr_base_op) / r_base_op))
â”‚     243â†’        theta8_op = jnp.pi - jnp.arccos(jd_math.clamp(jd_math.mult(body_i.base_normals[op_i], dr_base_op) / r_base_op))
â”‚     244â†’
â”‚     245â†’        v_hb = dna1_interactions.hydrogen_bonding(
â”‚     246â†’            dr_base_op,
â”‚     247â†’            theta1_op,
â”‚     248â†’            theta2_op,
â”‚     249â†’            theta3_op,
â”‚     250â†’            theta4_op,
â”‚     251â†’            theta7_op,
â”‚     252â†’            theta8_op,
â”‚     253â†’            self.params.dr_low_hb,
â”‚     254â†’            self.params.dr_high_hb,
â”‚     255â†’            self.params.dr_c_low_hb,
â”‚     256â†’            self.params.dr_c_high_hb,
â”‚     257â†’            self.params.eps_hb,
â”‚     258â†’            self.params.a_hb,
â”‚     259â†’            self.params.dr0_hb,
â”‚     260â†’            self.params.dr_c_hb,
â”‚     261â†’            self.params.b_low_hb,
â”‚     262â†’            self.params.b_high_hb,
â”‚     263â†’            self.params.theta0_hb_1,
â”‚     264â†’            self.params.delta_theta_star_hb_1,
â”‚     265â†’            self.params.a_hb_1,
â”‚     266â†’            self.params.delta_theta_hb_1_c,
â”‚     267â†’            self.params.b_hb_1,
â”‚     268â†’            self.params.theta0_hb_2,
â”‚     269â†’            self.params.delta_theta_star_hb_2,
â”‚     270â†’            self.params.a_hb_2,
â”‚     271â†’            self.params.delta_theta_hb_2_c,
â”‚     272â†’            self.params.b_hb_2,
â”‚     273â†’            self.params.theta0_hb_3,
â”‚     274â†’            self.params.delta_theta_star_hb_3,
â”‚     275â†’            self.params.a_hb_3,
â”‚     276â†’            self.params.delta_theta_hb_3_c,
â”‚     277â†’            self.params.b_hb_3,
â”‚     278â†’            self.params.theta0_hb_4,
â”‚     279â†’            self.params.delta_theta_star_hb_4,
â”‚     280â†’            self.params.a_hb_4,
â”‚     281â†’            self.params.delta_theta_hb_4_c,
â”‚     282â†’            self.params.b_hb_4,
â”‚     283â†’            self.params.theta0_hb_7,
â”‚     284â†’            self.params.delta_theta_star_hb_7,
â”‚     285â†’            self.params.a_hb_7,
â”‚     286â†’            self.params.delta_theta_hb_7_c,
â”‚     287â†’            self.params.b_hb_7,
â”‚     288â†’            self.params.theta0_hb_8,
â”‚     289â†’            self.params.delta_theta_star_hb_8,
â”‚     290â†’            self.params.a_hb_8,
â”‚     291â†’            self.params.delta_theta_hb_8_c,
â”‚     292â†’            self.params.b_hb_8,
â”‚     293â†’        )
â”‚     294â†’
â”‚     295â†’        return jnp.where(mask, v_hb, 0.0)  # Mask for neighbors
â”‚     296â†’
â”‚     297â†’    def pairwise_energies(
â”‚     298â†’        self,
â”‚     299â†’        body_i: je_base.BaseNucleotide,
â”‚     300â†’        body_j: je_base.BaseNucleotide,

"""Hydrogen bonding energy function for DNA1 model - PyTorch NPU version."""

from dataclasses import dataclass
from typing import Optional
import torch
import numpy as np

from jax_dna_npu.energy.base import BaseEnergyFunction
from jax_dna_npu.energy.configuration import BaseConfiguration
from jax_dna_npu.energy.dna1.nucleotide import Nucleotide
import jax_dna_npu.energy.dna1.base_smoothing_functions as bsf
import jax_dna_npu.energy.dna1.interactions as dna1_interactions
import jax_dna_npu.utils.math as jd_math
import jax_dna_npu.utils.types as typ


# Default hydrogen bonding weights (Watson-Crick base pairing)
HB_WEIGHTS_SA = torch.tensor([
    [0.0, 0.0, 0.0, 1.0],  # AX -> AT
    [0.0, 0.0, 1.0, 0.0],  # CX -> CG
    [0.0, 1.0, 0.0, 0.0],  # GX -> GC
    [1.0, 0.0, 0.0, 0.0],  # TX -> TA
])


@dataclass
class HydrogenBondingConfiguration(BaseConfiguration):
    """Configuration for the hydrogen bonding energy function."""

    # Independent parameters - f1(dr_hb)
    eps_hb: Optional[float] = None
    a_hb: Optional[float] = None
    dr0_hb: Optional[float] = None
    dr_c_hb: Optional[float] = None
    dr_low_hb: Optional[float] = None
    dr_high_hb: Optional[float] = None

    # f4(theta_1)
    a_hb_1: Optional[float] = None
    theta0_hb_1: Optional[float] = None
    delta_theta_star_hb_1: Optional[float] = None

    # f4(theta_2)
    a_hb_2: Optional[float] = None
    theta0_hb_2: Optional[float] = None
    delta_theta_star_hb_2: Optional[float] = None

    # f4(theta_3)
    a_hb_3: Optional[float] = None
    theta0_hb_3: Optional[float] = None
    delta_theta_star_hb_3: Optional[float] = None

    # f4(theta_4)
    a_hb_4: Optional[float] = None
    theta0_hb_4: Optional[float] = None
    delta_theta_star_hb_4: Optional[float] = None

    # f4(theta_7)
    a_hb_7: Optional[float] = None
    theta0_hb_7: Optional[float] = None
    delta_theta_star_hb_7: Optional[float] = None

    # f4(theta_8)
    a_hb_8: Optional[float] = None
    theta0_hb_8: Optional[float] = None
    delta_theta_star_hb_8: Optional[float] = None

    # Sequence-dependence weights
    ss_hb_weights: Optional[np.ndarray] = None

    # Dependent parameters
    b_low_hb: Optional[float] = None
    dr_c_low_hb: Optional[float] = None
    b_high_hb: Optional[float] = None
    dr_c_high_hb: Optional[float] = None
    b_hb_1: Optional[float] = None
    delta_theta_hb_1_c: Optional[float] = None
    b_hb_2: Optional[float] = None
    delta_theta_hb_2_c: Optional[float] = None
    b_hb_3: Optional[float] = None
    delta_theta_hb_3_c: Optional[float] = None
    b_hb_4: Optional[float] = None
    delta_theta_hb_4_c: Optional[float] = None
    b_hb_7: Optional[float] = None
    delta_theta_hb_7_c: Optional[float] = None
    b_hb_8: Optional[float] = None
    delta_theta_hb_8_c: Optional[float] = None

    required_params: tuple[str, ...] = (
        "eps_hb",
        "a_hb",
        "dr0_hb",
        "dr_c_hb",
        "dr_low_hb",
        "dr_high_hb",
        "a_hb_1",
        "theta0_hb_1",
        "delta_theta_star_hb_1",
        "a_hb_2",
        "theta0_hb_2",
        "delta_theta_star_hb_2",
        "a_hb_3",
        "theta0_hb_3",
        "delta_theta_star_hb_3",
        "a_hb_4",
        "theta0_hb_4",
        "delta_theta_star_hb_4",
        "a_hb_7",
        "theta0_hb_7",
        "delta_theta_star_hb_7",
        "a_hb_8",
        "theta0_hb_8",
        "delta_theta_star_hb_8",
    )

    dependent_params: tuple[str, ...] = (
        "b_low_hb",
        "dr_c_low_hb",
        "b_high_hb",
        "dr_c_high_hb",
        "b_hb_1",
        "delta_theta_hb_1_c",
        "b_hb_2",
        "delta_theta_hb_2_c",
        "b_hb_3",
        "delta_theta_hb_3_c",
        "b_hb_4",
        "delta_theta_hb_4_c",
        "b_hb_7",
        "delta_theta_hb_7_c",
        "b_hb_8",
        "delta_theta_hb_8_c",
    )

    def __post_init__(self):
        """Initialize default HB weights if not provided."""
        if self.ss_hb_weights is None:
            object.__setattr__(self, 'ss_hb_weights', HB_WEIGHTS_SA.numpy())

    def init_params(self) -> "HydrogenBondingConfiguration":
        """Initialize dependent parameters from independent parameters."""
        # f1(dr_hb)
        b_low_hb, dr_c_low_hb, b_high_hb, dr_c_high_hb = bsf.get_f1_smoothing_params(
            self.dr0_hb,
            self.a_hb,
            self.dr_c_hb,
            self.dr_low_hb,
            self.dr_high_hb,
        )

        # f4 parameters for all theta angles
        b_hb_1, delta_theta_hb_1_c = bsf.get_f4_smoothing_params(
            self.a_hb_1, self.theta0_hb_1, self.delta_theta_star_hb_1
        )
        b_hb_2, delta_theta_hb_2_c = bsf.get_f4_smoothing_params(
            self.a_hb_2, self.theta0_hb_2, self.delta_theta_star_hb_2
        )
        b_hb_3, delta_theta_hb_3_c = bsf.get_f4_smoothing_params(
            self.a_hb_3, self.theta0_hb_3, self.delta_theta_star_hb_3
        )
        b_hb_4, delta_theta_hb_4_c = bsf.get_f4_smoothing_params(
            self.a_hb_4, self.theta0_hb_4, self.delta_theta_star_hb_4
        )
        b_hb_7, delta_theta_hb_7_c = bsf.get_f4_smoothing_params(
            self.a_hb_7, self.theta0_hb_7, self.delta_theta_star_hb_7
        )
        b_hb_8, delta_theta_hb_8_c = bsf.get_f4_smoothing_params(
            self.a_hb_8, self.theta0_hb_8, self.delta_theta_star_hb_8
        )

        # Convert tensors to floats
        def to_float(x):
            return float(x.item()) if isinstance(x, torch.Tensor) else float(x)

        return HydrogenBondingConfiguration(
            params_to_optimize=self.params_to_optimize,
            required_params=self.required_params,
            non_optimizable_required_params=self.non_optimizable_required_params,
            dependent_params=self.dependent_params,
            eps_hb=self.eps_hb,
            a_hb=self.a_hb,
            dr0_hb=self.dr0_hb,
            dr_c_hb=self.dr_c_hb,
            dr_low_hb=self.dr_low_hb,
            dr_high_hb=self.dr_high_hb,
            a_hb_1=self.a_hb_1,
            theta0_hb_1=self.theta0_hb_1,
            delta_theta_star_hb_1=self.delta_theta_star_hb_1,
            a_hb_2=self.a_hb_2,
            theta0_hb_2=self.theta0_hb_2,
            delta_theta_star_hb_2=self.delta_theta_star_hb_2,
            a_hb_3=self.a_hb_3,
            theta0_hb_3=self.theta0_hb_3,
            delta_theta_star_hb_3=self.delta_theta_star_hb_3,
            a_hb_4=self.a_hb_4,
            theta0_hb_4=self.theta0_hb_4,
            delta_theta_star_hb_4=self.delta_theta_star_hb_4,
            a_hb_7=self.a_hb_7,
            theta0_hb_7=self.theta0_hb_7,
            delta_theta_star_hb_7=self.delta_theta_star_hb_7,
            a_hb_8=self.a_hb_8,
            theta0_hb_8=self.theta0_hb_8,
            delta_theta_star_hb_8=self.delta_theta_star_hb_8,
            ss_hb_weights=self.ss_hb_weights,
            b_low_hb=to_float(b_low_hb),
            dr_c_low_hb=to_float(dr_c_low_hb),
            b_high_hb=to_float(b_high_hb),
            dr_c_high_hb=to_float(dr_c_high_hb),
            b_hb_1=to_float(b_hb_1),
            delta_theta_hb_1_c=to_float(delta_theta_hb_1_c),
            b_hb_2=to_float(b_hb_2),
            delta_theta_hb_2_c=to_float(delta_theta_hb_2_c),
            b_hb_3=to_float(b_hb_3),
            delta_theta_hb_3_c=to_float(delta_theta_hb_3_c),
            b_hb_4=to_float(b_hb_4),
            delta_theta_hb_4_c=to_float(delta_theta_hb_4_c),
            b_hb_7=to_float(b_hb_7),
            delta_theta_hb_7_c=to_float(delta_theta_hb_7_c),
            b_hb_8=to_float(b_hb_8),
            delta_theta_hb_8_c=to_float(delta_theta_hb_8_c),
        )


class HydrogenBonding(BaseEnergyFunction):
    """Hydrogen bonding energy function for DNA1 model."""

    def __init__(self, params: HydrogenBondingConfiguration, displacement_fn=None):
        """Initialize the hydrogen bonding energy function.

        Args:
            params: Configuration parameters
            displacement_fn: Optional custom displacement function
        """
        super().__init__(displacement_fn)
        self.params = params

        # Initialize dependent parameters if needed
        if any(getattr(params, name) is None for name in params.dependent_params):
            self.params = params.init_params()

        # Register optimizable parameters
        if params.params_to_optimize:
            for name, value in params.opt_params_torch.items():
                self.register_parameter(f'param_{name}', value)

        # Register HB weights as buffer (not trainable by default)
        if params.ss_hb_weights is not None:
            self.register_buffer(
                'hb_weights',
                torch.as_tensor(params.ss_hb_weights, dtype=torch.float32)
            )
        else:
            self.register_buffer('hb_weights', HB_WEIGHTS_SA)

    def compute_v_hb(
        self,
        nucleotides_i: Nucleotide,
        nucleotides_j: Nucleotide,
        unbonded_neighbors: torch.Tensor,
    ) -> torch.Tensor:
        """Compute the sequence-independent energy for each unbonded pair.

        Args:
            nucleotides_i: First nucleotide structure
            nucleotides_j: Second nucleotide structure (usually same as first)
            unbonded_neighbors: Unbonded neighbor pairs (2, M)

        Returns:
            Energy for each unbonded pair (M,)
        """
        op_i = unbonded_neighbors[0].long()
        op_j = unbonded_neighbors[1].long()

        # Create mask to filter invalid pairs
        mask = (op_i < nucleotides_i.centers.shape[0]).float()

        # Displacement vector between base sites
        dr_base_op = self._displacement_fn(
            nucleotides_j.base_sites[op_j],
            nucleotides_i.base_sites[op_i]
        )
        r_base_op = torch.linalg.norm(dr_base_op, dim=1)

        # Compute all angles
        theta1_op = torch.arccos(
            jd_math.clamp(jd_math.mult(
                -nucleotides_i.back_base_vectors[op_i],
                nucleotides_j.back_base_vectors[op_j]
            ))
        )
        theta2_op = torch.arccos(
            jd_math.clamp(jd_math.mult(
                -nucleotides_j.back_base_vectors[op_j],
                dr_base_op
            ) / r_base_op)
        )
        theta3_op = torch.arccos(
            jd_math.clamp(jd_math.mult(
                nucleotides_i.back_base_vectors[op_i],
                dr_base_op
            ) / r_base_op)
        )
        theta4_op = torch.arccos(
            jd_math.clamp(jd_math.mult(
                nucleotides_i.base_normals[op_i],
                nucleotides_j.base_normals[op_j]
            ))
        )
        theta7_op = torch.arccos(
            jd_math.clamp(jd_math.mult(
                -nucleotides_j.base_normals[op_j],
                dr_base_op
            ) / r_base_op)
        )
        theta8_op = torch.pi - torch.arccos(
            jd_math.clamp(jd_math.mult(
                nucleotides_i.base_normals[op_i],
                dr_base_op
            ) / r_base_op)
        )

        v_hb = dna1_interactions.hydrogen_bonding(
            dr_base_op,
            theta1_op,
            theta2_op,
            theta3_op,
            theta4_op,
            theta7_op,
            theta8_op,
            self.params.dr_low_hb,
            self.params.dr_high_hb,
            self.params.dr_c_low_hb,
            self.params.dr_c_high_hb,
            self.params.eps_hb,
            self.params.a_hb,
            self.params.dr0_hb,
            self.params.dr_c_hb,
            self.params.b_low_hb,
            self.params.b_high_hb,
            self.params.theta0_hb_1,
            self.params.delta_theta_star_hb_1,
            self.params.a_hb_1,
            self.params.delta_theta_hb_1_c,
            self.params.b_hb_1,
            self.params.theta0_hb_2,
            self.params.delta_theta_star_hb_2,
            self.params.a_hb_2,
            self.params.delta_theta_hb_2_c,
            self.params.b_hb_2,
            self.params.theta0_hb_3,
            self.params.delta_theta_star_hb_3,
            self.params.a_hb_3,
            self.params.delta_theta_hb_3_c,
            self.params.b_hb_3,
            self.params.theta0_hb_4,
            self.params.delta_theta_star_hb_4,
            self.params.a_hb_4,
            self.params.delta_theta_hb_4_c,
            self.params.b_hb_4,
            self.params.theta0_hb_7,
            self.params.delta_theta_star_hb_7,
            self.params.a_hb_7,
            self.params.delta_theta_hb_7_c,
            self.params.b_hb_7,
            self.params.theta0_hb_8,
            self.params.delta_theta_star_hb_8,
            self.params.a_hb_8,
            self.params.delta_theta_hb_8_c,
            self.params.b_hb_8,
        )

        return torch.where(mask.bool(), v_hb, torch.zeros_like(v_hb))

    def pairwise_energies(
        self,
        nucleotides_i: Nucleotide,
        nucleotides_j: Nucleotide,
        seq: typ.Sequence,
        unbonded_neighbors: torch.Tensor,
    ) -> torch.Tensor:
        """Compute the hydrogen bonding energy for each unbonded pair.

        Args:
            nucleotides_i: First nucleotide structure
            nucleotides_j: Second nucleotide structure (usually same as first)
            seq: Nucleotide sequence
            unbonded_neighbors: Unbonded neighbor pairs (2, M)

        Returns:
            Energy for each unbonded pair (M,)
        """
        # Compute sequence-independent energy for each unbonded pair
        v_hb = self.compute_v_hb(nucleotides_i, nucleotides_j, unbonded_neighbors)

        # Compute sequence-dependent weight for each unbonded pair
        op_i = unbonded_neighbors[0].long()
        op_j = unbonded_neighbors[1].long()

        # Convert sequence to tensor if needed
        if isinstance(seq, (list, tuple)):
            seq = torch.tensor(seq, dtype=torch.long)

        hb_weights = self.hb_weights[seq[op_i], seq[op_j]]

        return hb_weights * v_hb

    def forward(
        self,
        positions: torch.Tensor,
        seq: typ.Sequence,
        bonded_neighbors: torch.Tensor,
        unbonded_neighbors: torch.Tensor,
        nucleotides: Optional[Nucleotide] = None,
        **kwargs
    ) -> torch.Tensor:
        """Calculate total hydrogen bonding energy.

        Args:
            positions: Nucleotide positions (can be centers or full structure)
            seq: Nucleotide sequence
            bonded_neighbors: Bonded neighbor pairs (not used)
            unbonded_neighbors: Unbonded neighbor pairs (2, M)
            nucleotides: Optional precomputed nucleotide structure
            **kwargs: Additional parameters

        Returns:
            Total hydrogen bonding energy (scalar tensor)
        """
        # If nucleotides not provided, assume positions are Nucleotide object
        if nucleotides is None:
            # Use attribute checking instead of isinstance to handle device transfers
            if hasattr(positions, 'base_sites') and hasattr(positions, 'back_base_vectors'):
                nucleotides = positions
            else:
                raise ValueError("Hydrogen bonding requires full Nucleotide structure")

        # Verify required attributes exist
        if nucleotides.back_base_vectors is None or nucleotides.base_normals is None:
            raise ValueError("Hydrogen bonding requires Nucleotide with back_base_vectors and base_normals")

        # Compute pairwise energies and sum
        dgs = self.pairwise_energies(nucleotides, nucleotides, seq, unbonded_neighbors)
        return dgs.sum()
EOF

Add DNA1 HydrogenBonding energy class

- Implement HydrogenBonding with Watson-Crick base pairing weights
- Support 6 angle-dependent terms (theta1-4, theta7-8)
- Include f1 distance smoothing and f4 angle smoothing
- Compute all angles from base_normals and back_base_vectors
- Apply sequence-dependent weights for base pair specificity

This completes the core DNA1 energy components. All classes follow
PyTorch nn.Module architecture with full NPU support.

### åŸºæœ¬èƒ½é‡é¡¹ï¼ˆç‰©ç†ç›¸äº’ä½œç”¨ï¼Œå¿…éœ€ï¼‰
**è¿™ 7 ä¸ªæ˜¯ç‹¬ç«‹çš„ç‰©ç†ç›¸äº’ä½œç”¨**ï¼Œæ¯ä¸ªæè¿°ä¸åŒçš„ç‰©ç†ç°è±¡ï¼š

**å®ƒä»¬ä¸èƒ½äº’ç›¸ç»„åˆæˆ–æ›¿ä»£ï¼** æ¯ä¸ªæè¿°ä¸åŒçš„ç‰©ç†æœºåˆ¶ã€‚

### "Expected" ç‰ˆæœ¬ï¼ˆç”¨äºåºåˆ—ä¼˜åŒ–ï¼‰
**ExpectedStacking** å’Œ **ExpectedHydrogenBonding** ä¸æ˜¯æ–°çš„ç‰©ç†é¡¹ï¼Œè€Œæ˜¯ï¼š

```python
# æ™®é€šç‰ˆæœ¬ï¼šç¡®å®šåºåˆ—
seq = [0, 1, 2, 3]  # A, C, G, T
E_stacking = Stacking(nucleotides, seq, ...)

# Expected ç‰ˆæœ¬ï¼šæ¦‚ç‡åºåˆ—
prob_seq = [
    [0.7, 0.1, 0.1, 0.1],  # ä½ç½®0: 70% A, 10% C, 10% G, 10% T
    [0.2, 0.6, 0.1, 0.1],  # ä½ç½®1: 20% A, 60% C, ...
    ...
]
E_expected = ExpectedStacking(nucleotides, prob_seq, ...)
# è®¡ç®—: Î£ P(åºåˆ—) Ã— E(åºåˆ—)
```

**ç”¨é€”**ï¼š
- åºåˆ—è®¾è®¡/ä¼˜åŒ–ï¼šç»™å®šç»“æ„ï¼Œæ‰¾æœ€ä¼˜åºåˆ—

- è®­ç»ƒ/å‚æ•°ä¼˜åŒ–ï¼šåœ¨åºåˆ—ç©ºé—´ä¸­æ±‚æ¢¯åº¦

â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€

â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€

â”‚  å‘½ä»¤: cat > /workspace/dna_study/jax_dna_npu/energy/dna1/cross_stacking.py << 'EOF'
"""Cross-stacking energy term for DNA1 model - PyTorch NPU version."""

from dataclasses import dataclass
from typing import Optional
import torch

from jax_dna_npu.energy.base import BaseEnergyFunction
from jax_dna_npu.energy.configuration import BaseConfiguration
from jax_dna_npu.energy.dna1.nucleotide import Nucleotide
import jax_dna_npu.energy.dna1.base_smoothing_functions as bsf
import jax_dna_npu.energy.dna1.interactions as dna1_interactions
import jax_dna_npu.utils.math as jd_math
import jax_dna_npu.utils.types as typ


@dataclass
class CrossStackingConfiguration(BaseConfiguration):
    """Configuration for the cross-stacking energy function."""

    # Independent parameters
    dr_low_cross: Optional[float] = None
    dr_high_cross: Optional[float] = None
    k_cross: Optional[float] = None
    r0_cross: Optional[float] = None
    dr_c_cross: Optional[float] = None
    theta0_cross_1: Optional[float] = None
    delta_theta_star_cross_1: Optional[float] = None
    a_cross_1: Optional[float] = None
    theta0_cross_2: Optional[float] = None
    delta_theta_star_cross_2: Optional[float] = None
    a_cross_2: Optional[float] = None
    theta0_cross_3: Optional[float] = None
    delta_theta_star_cross_3: Optional[float] = None
    a_cross_3: Optional[float] = None
    theta0_cross_4: Optional[float] = None
    delta_theta_star_cross_4: Optional[float] = None
    a_cross_4: Optional[float] = None
    theta0_cross_7: Optional[float] = None
    delta_theta_star_cross_7: Optional[float] = None
    a_cross_7: Optional[float] = None
    theta0_cross_8: Optional[float] = None
    delta_theta_star_cross_8: Optional[float] = None
    a_cross_8: Optional[float] = None

    # Dependent parameters
    b_low_cross: Optional[float] = None
    dr_c_low_cross: Optional[float] = None
    b_high_cross: Optional[float] = None
    dr_c_high_cross: Optional[float] = None
    b_cross_1: Optional[float] = None
    delta_theta_cross_1_c: Optional[float] = None
    b_cross_2: Optional[float] = None
    delta_theta_cross_2_c: Optional[float] = None
    b_cross_3: Optional[float] = None
    delta_theta_cross_3_c: Optional[float] = None
    b_cross_4: Optional[float] = None
    delta_theta_cross_4_c: Optional[float] = None
    b_cross_7: Optional[float] = None
    delta_theta_cross_7_c: Optional[float] = None
    b_cross_8: Optional[float] = None
    delta_theta_cross_8_c: Optional[float] = None

    required_params: tuple[str, ...] = (
        "dr_low_cross",
        "dr_high_cross",
        "k_cross",
        "r0_cross",
        "dr_c_cross",
        "theta0_cross_1",
        "delta_theta_star_cross_1",
        "a_cross_1",
        "theta0_cross_2",
        "delta_theta_star_cross_2",
        "a_cross_2",
        "theta0_cross_3",
        "delta_theta_star_cross_3",
        "a_cross_3",
        "theta0_cross_4",
        "delta_theta_star_cross_4",
        "a_cross_4",
        "theta0_cross_7",
        "delta_theta_star_cross_7",
        "a_cross_7",
        "theta0_cross_8",
        "delta_theta_star_cross_8",
        "a_cross_8",
    )

    dependent_params: tuple[str, ...] = (
        "b_low_cross",
        "dr_c_low_cross",
        "b_high_cross",
        "dr_c_high_cross",
        "b_cross_1",
        "delta_theta_cross_1_c",
        "b_cross_2",
        "delta_theta_cross_2_c",
        "b_cross_3",
        "delta_theta_cross_3_c",
        "b_cross_4",
        "delta_theta_cross_4_c",
        "b_cross_7",
        "delta_theta_cross_7_c",
        "b_cross_8",
        "delta_theta_cross_8_c",
    )

    def init_params(self) -> "CrossStackingConfiguration":
        """Initialize dependent parameters from independent parameters."""
        # f2 smoothing for distance
        (
            b_low_cross,
            dr_c_low_cross,
            b_high_cross,
            dr_c_high_cross,
        ) = bsf.get_f2_smoothing_params(
            self.r0_cross,
            self.dr_c_cross,
            self.dr_low_cross,
            self.dr_high_cross,
        )

        # f4 parameters for all theta angles
        b_cross_1, delta_theta_cross_1_c = bsf.get_f4_smoothing_params(
            self.a_cross_1, self.theta0_cross_1, self.delta_theta_star_cross_1
        )
        b_cross_2, delta_theta_cross_2_c = bsf.get_f4_smoothing_params(
            self.a_cross_2, self.theta0_cross_2, self.delta_theta_star_cross_2
        )
        b_cross_3, delta_theta_cross_3_c = bsf.get_f4_smoothing_params(
            self.a_cross_3, self.theta0_cross_3, self.delta_theta_star_cross_3
        )
        b_cross_4, delta_theta_cross_4_c = bsf.get_f4_smoothing_params(
            self.a_cross_4, self.theta0_cross_4, self.delta_theta_star_cross_4
        )
        b_cross_7, delta_theta_cross_7_c = bsf.get_f4_smoothing_params(
            self.a_cross_7, self.theta0_cross_7, self.delta_theta_star_cross_7
        )
        b_cross_8, delta_theta_cross_8_c = bsf.get_f4_smoothing_params(
            self.a_cross_8, self.theta0_cross_8, self.delta_theta_star_cross_8
        )

        # Convert tensors to floats
        def to_float(x):
            return float(x.item()) if isinstance(x, torch.Tensor) else float(x)

        return CrossStackingConfiguration(
            params_to_optimize=self.params_to_optimize,
            required_params=self.required_params,
            non_optimizable_required_params=self.non_optimizable_required_params,
            dependent_params=self.dependent_params,
            dr_low_cross=self.dr_low_cross,
            dr_high_cross=self.dr_high_cross,
            k_cross=self.k_cross,
            r0_cross=self.r0_cross,
            dr_c_cross=self.dr_c_cross,
            theta0_cross_1=self.theta0_cross_1,
            delta_theta_star_cross_1=self.delta_theta_star_cross_1,
            a_cross_1=self.a_cross_1,
            theta0_cross_2=self.theta0_cross_2,
            delta_theta_star_cross_2=self.delta_theta_star_cross_2,
            a_cross_2=self.a_cross_2,
            theta0_cross_3=self.theta0_cross_3,
            delta_theta_star_cross_3=self.delta_theta_star_cross_3,
            a_cross_3=self.a_cross_3,
            theta0_cross_4=self.theta0_cross_4,
            delta_theta_star_cross_4=self.delta_theta_star_cross_4,
            a_cross_4=self.a_cross_4,
            theta0_cross_7=self.theta0_cross_7,
            delta_theta_star_cross_7=self.delta_theta_star_cross_7,
            a_cross_7=self.a_cross_7,
            theta0_cross_8=self.theta0_cross_8,
            delta_theta_star_cross_8=self.delta_theta_star_cross_8,
            a_cross_8=self.a_cross_8,
            b_low_cross=to_float(b_low_cross),
            dr_c_low_cross=to_float(dr_c_low_cross),
            b_high_cross=to_float(b_high_cross),
            dr_c_high_cross=to_float(dr_c_high_cross),
            b_cross_1=to_float(b_cross_1),
            delta_theta_cross_1_c=to_float(delta_theta_cross_1_c),
            b_cross_2=to_float(b_cross_2),
            delta_theta_cross_2_c=to_float(delta_theta_cross_2_c),
            b_cross_3=to_float(b_cross_3),
            delta_theta_cross_3_c=to_float(delta_theta_cross_3_c),
            b_cross_4=to_float(b_cross_4),
            delta_theta_cross_4_c=to_float(delta_theta_cross_4_c),
            b_cross_7=to_float(b_cross_7),
            delta_theta_cross_7_c=to_float(delta_theta_cross_7_c),
            b_cross_8=to_float(b_cross_8),
            delta_theta_cross_8_c=to_float(delta_theta_cross_8_c),
        )


class CrossStacking(BaseEnergyFunction):
    """Cross-stacking energy function for DNA1 model."""

    def __init__(self, params: CrossStackingConfiguration, displacement_fn=None):
        """Initialize the cross-stacking energy function.

        Args:
            params: Configuration parameters
            displacement_fn: Optional custom displacement function
        """
        super().__init__(displacement_fn)
        self.params = params

        # Initialize dependent parameters if needed
        if any(getattr(params, name) is None for name in params.dependent_params):
            self.params = params.init_params()

        # Register optimizable parameters
        if params.params_to_optimize:
            for name, value in params.opt_params_torch.items():
                self.register_parameter(f'param_{name}', value)

    def pairwise_energies(
        self,
        nucleotides_i: Nucleotide,
        nucleotides_j: Nucleotide,
        unbonded_neighbors: torch.Tensor,
    ) -> torch.Tensor:
        """Compute the cross stacking energy for each unbonded pair.

        Args:
            nucleotides_i: First nucleotide structure
            nucleotides_j: Second nucleotide structure (usually same as first)
            unbonded_neighbors: Unbonded neighbor pairs (2, M)

        Returns:
            Energy for each unbonded pair (M,)
        """
        op_i = unbonded_neighbors[0].long()
        op_j = unbonded_neighbors[1].long()

        # Create mask to filter invalid pairs
        mask = (op_i < nucleotides_i.centers.shape[0]).float()

        # Displacement vector between base sites
        dr_base_op = self._displacement_fn(
            nucleotides_j.base_sites[op_j],
            nucleotides_i.base_sites[op_i]
        )
        r_base_op = torch.linalg.norm(dr_base_op, dim=1)

        # Compute all angles (same as HydrogenBonding)
        theta1_op = torch.arccos(
            jd_math.clamp(jd_math.mult(
                -nucleotides_i.back_base_vectors[op_i],
                nucleotides_j.back_base_vectors[op_j]
            ))
        )
        theta2_op = torch.arccos(
            jd_math.clamp(jd_math.mult(
                -nucleotides_j.back_base_vectors[op_j],
                dr_base_op
            ) / r_base_op)
        )
        theta3_op = torch.arccos(
            jd_math.clamp(jd_math.mult(
                nucleotides_i.back_base_vectors[op_i],
                dr_base_op
            ) / r_base_op)
        )
        theta4_op = torch.arccos(
            jd_math.clamp(jd_math.mult(
                nucleotides_i.base_normals[op_i],
                nucleotides_j.base_normals[op_j]
            ))
        )
        theta7_op = torch.arccos(
            jd_math.clamp(jd_math.mult(
                -nucleotides_j.base_normals[op_j],
                dr_base_op
            ) / r_base_op)
        )
        theta8_op = torch.pi - torch.arccos(
            jd_math.clamp(jd_math.mult(
                nucleotides_i.base_normals[op_i],
                dr_base_op
            ) / r_base_op)
        )

        cr_stack_dg = dna1_interactions.cross_stacking(
            r_base_op,
            theta1_op,
            theta2_op,
            theta3_op,
            theta4_op,
            theta7_op,
            theta8_op,
            self.params.dr_low_cross,
            self.params.dr_high_cross,
            self.params.dr_c_low_cross,
            self.params.dr_c_high_cross,
            self.params.k_cross,
            self.params.r0_cross,
            self.params.dr_c_cross,
            self.params.b_low_cross,
            self.params.b_high_cross,
            self.params.theta0_cross_1,
            self.params.delta_theta_star_cross_1,
            self.params.delta_theta_cross_1_c,
            self.params.a_cross_1,
            self.params.b_cross_1,
            self.params.theta0_cross_2,
            self.params.delta_theta_star_cross_2,
            self.params.delta_theta_cross_2_c,
            self.params.a_cross_2,
            self.params.b_cross_2,
            self.params.theta0_cross_3,
            self.params.delta_theta_star_cross_3,
            self.params.delta_theta_cross_3_c,
            self.params.a_cross_3,
            self.params.b_cross_3,
            self.params.theta0_cross_4,
            self.params.delta_theta_star_cross_4,
            self.params.delta_theta_cross_4_c,
            self.params.a_cross_4,
            self.params.b_cross_4,
            self.params.theta0_cross_7,
            self.params.delta_theta_star_cross_7,
            self.params.delta_theta_cross_7_c,
            self.params.a_cross_7,
            self.params.b_cross_7,
            self.params.theta0_cross_8,
            self.params.delta_theta_star_cross_8,
            self.params.delta_theta_cross_8_c,
            self.params.a_cross_8,
            self.params.b_cross_8,
        )

        return torch.where(mask.bool(), cr_stack_dg, torch.zeros_like(cr_stack_dg))

    def forward(
        self,
        positions: torch.Tensor,
        seq: typ.Sequence,
        bonded_neighbors: torch.Tensor,
        unbonded_neighbors: torch.Tensor,
        nucleotides: Optional[Nucleotide] = None,
        **kwargs
    ) -> torch.Tensor:
        """Calculate total cross-stacking energy.

        Args:
            positions: Nucleotide positions (can be centers or full structure)
            seq: Nucleotide sequence
            bonded_neighbors: Bonded neighbor pairs (not used)
            unbonded_neighbors: Unbonded neighbor pairs (2, M)
            nucleotides: Optional precomputed nucleotide structure
            **kwargs: Additional parameters

        Returns:
            Total cross-stacking energy (scalar tensor)
        """
        # If nucleotides not provided, assume positions are Nucleotide object
        if nucleotides is None:
            if hasattr(positions, 'base_sites') and hasattr(positions, 'back_base_vectors'):
                nucleotides = positions
            else:
                raise ValueError("Cross-stacking requires full Nucleotide structure")

        # Verify required attributes exist
        if nucleotides.back_base_vectors is None or nucleotides.base_normals is None:
            raise ValueError("Cross-stacking requires Nucleotide with back_base_vectors and base_normals")

        # Compute pairwise energies and sum
        dgs = self.pairwise_energies(nucleotides, nucleotides, unbonded_neighbors)
        return dgs.sum()

â”‚     177â†’    """Coaxial stacking energy function for DNA1 model."""
â”‚     178â†’
â”‚     179â†’    params: CoaxialStackingConfiguration
â”‚     180â†’
â”‚     181â†’    def pairwise_energies(
â”‚     182â†’        self,
â”‚     183â†’        body_i: je_base.BaseNucleotide,
â”‚     184â†’        body_j: je_base.BaseNucleotide,
â”‚     185â†’        unbonded_neighbors: typ.Arr_Unbonded_Neighbors_2,
â”‚     186â†’    ) -> typ.Arr_Unbonded_Neighbors:
â”‚     187â†’        """Computes the coaxial stacking energy for each unbonded pair."""
â”‚     188â†’        op_i = unbonded_neighbors[0]
â”‚     189â†’        op_j = unbonded_neighbors[1]
â”‚     190â†’        mask = jnp.array(op_i < body_i.center.shape[0], dtype=jnp.float32)
â”‚     191â†’
â”‚     192â†’        dr_stack_op = self.displacement_mapped(body_j.stack_sites[op_j], body_i.stack_sites[op_i])
â”‚     193â†’        dr_stack_norm_op = dr_stack_op / jnp.linalg.norm(dr_stack_op, axis=1, keepdims=True)
â”‚     194â†’        dr_backbone_op = self.displacement_mapped(body_j.back_sites[op_j], body_i.back_sites[op_i])
â”‚     195â†’        dr_backbone_norm_op = dr_backbone_op / jnp.linalg.norm(dr_backbone_op, axis=1, keepdims=True)
â”‚     196â†’
â”‚     197â†’        theta4_op = jnp.arccos(
â”‚     198â†’            jd_math.clamp(jnp.einsum("ij, ij->i", body_i.base_normals[op_i], body_j.base_normals[op_j]))
â”‚     199â†’        )
â”‚     200â†’        theta1_op = jnp.arccos(
